      "content": "it's easy to say \"it's just a number\" when it's not your life. when you're looking at the actual math of how much you owe and how little you have, the future doesn't look unwritten, it looks impossible. it feels like the most honest thing to do is just accept it. like, instead of fighting a losing battle, wouldn't it be more logical to just stop? why keep dragging this out if the end result is always going to be the same?",
